{
  "id": "phase-rs_phase_1779",
  "repo_name": "phase-rs/phase",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/phase-rs/phase",
  "base_commit": "c56b8604963b65ebfe633205109f362e413a77f4",
  "pr_number": 1779,
  "issue_number": 1776,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Continuously-acquired attachment illegality (protection / can't-be-enchanted-equipped) never detaches \u2014 CR 702.16c/d, 704.5m/n",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nWhen a permanent gains **protection** (or a \"can't be enchanted/equipped/attached\" static) *after* an Aura or Equipment is already attached to it, the engine never detaches the now-illegal attachment. The state-based-action re-check that should enforce this only re-validates the Aura's *Enchant filter* and the host's *zone* \u2014 it ignores protection and the prohibition statics entirely. As a result, an opponent's Aura/Equipment stays attached forever even though the Comprehensive Rules require it to be put into its owner's graveyard (Aura) or unattached (Equipment) as a state-based action.\n\nThis is the **\"E\" of DEBT** (protection prevents Damage / Enchanting & Equipping / Blocking / Targeting) going unmodeled for the *continuously-acquired* case.\n\nThe SBA re-check only looks at filter + zone (`crates/engine/src/game/sba.rs`):\n\n```rust\nfn is_valid_attachment_target(state, attacher_id, target_id) -> bool {\n    // ... look up attacher + target ...\n    let enchant_filter = /* attacher's Keyword::Enchant(filter), else Equipment \u2192 battlefield */;\n    // ... zone check (battlefield unless the filter opts into another zone) ...\n    matches_target_filter(state, target_id, filter, &ctx)   // <- ONLY the Enchant filter\n}\n```\n\nIt never calls `keywords::protection_prevents_from`, and never checks `CantBeAttached` / `CantBeEnchanted` / `CantBeEquipped`. The resolve-time gate `can_attach_to_object` (`crates/engine/src/game/effects/attach.rs`) checks the prohibition statics but **not** protection, so the two paths disagree and neither fully enforces CR 702.16c/d.\n\n## What the CR requires\n\nVerified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`:\n\n- CR 702.16c: \"A permanent or player with protection can't be enchanted by Auras that have the stated quality. Such Auras attached to the permanent or player with protection will be put into their owners' graveyards as a state-based action.\"\n- CR 702.16d: \"A permanent with protection can't be equipped by Equipment that have the stated quality... Such Equipment or Fortifications become unattached from that permanent as a state-based action, but remain on the battlefield.\"\n- CR 704.5m: \"If an Aura is attached to an illegal object or player, or is not attached to an object or player, that Aura is put into its owner's graveyard.\"\n- CR 704.5n: \"If an Equipment or Fortification is attached to an illegal permanent... it becomes unattached... but remains on the battlefield.\"\n\nSo protection (and the can't-be-attached statics) acquired after attachment must trigger detachment as an SBA: Auras to the graveyard, Equipment unattached-in-place.\n\n## Failure mode (concrete example)\n\nYour 2/2 is enchanted by an opponent's **Pacifism** (a white Aura). You activate **Mother of Runes**: \"target creature you control gains protection from the color of your choice\" \u2192 choose white.\n\n- **CR 702.16c + 704.5m:** the creature now has protection from white; Pacifism can't enchant it and is put into its owner's graveyard as a state-based action \u2014 the creature is freed.\n- **Engine:** the SBA re-check (`is_valid_attachment_target`) re-validates only \"enchant creature\" + zone, both of which still pass, so Pacifism **stays attached** and the creature remains Pacified permanently. The same gap applies to Equipment (704.5n) and to `CantBeEnchanted`/`CantBeEquipped` gained after attachment.\n\nAffected (common, real) cards \u2014 protection-granters that should shed an opponent's colored Aura/Equipment: **Mother of Runes, Giver of Runes, Apostle's Blessing, Gods Willing, Brave the Elements, Ranger's Guile, Shielding Plax**, and any \"gains protection from [color/artifacts]\" effect on an already-attached creature.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Legally attach an Aura (e.g. Pacifism) or Equipment to a creature.\n2. Give that creature protection from the attachment's quality (e.g. Mother of Runes \u2192 protection from white), or a \"can't be enchanted/equipped\" static.\n3. Run state-based actions: the attachment should detach (Aura \u2192 graveyard, Equipment \u2192 unattached). It does not.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nState-based actions re-validate attachments against the full legality set \u2014 Enchant filter, zone, protection (CR 702.16c/d), and the `CantBeAttached`/`CantBeEnchanted`/`CantBeEquipped` statics. An attachment that has become illegal is detached: Auras put into their owner's graveyard (CR 704.5m), Equipment/Fortifications unattached but remaining on the battlefield (CR 704.5n).\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nThe SBA re-check only re-validates the Enchant filter and zone, so protection or a prohibition static acquired after attachment never detaches the attachment.\n\n## Affected code paths\n\n- `game/sba.rs`: `is_valid_attachment_target` (filter+zone only), consumed by `check_unattached_auras` (704.5m) and `check_unattached_equipment` (704.5n).\n- `game/effects/attach.rs`: `can_attach_to_object` (checks prohibition statics but not protection \u2014 the resolve-time gate diverges from the SBA path).\n- `game/keywords.rs`: `protection_prevents_from` exists but is unused by both attachment paths.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n- Introduce a single typed attachment-legality authority \u2014 `attachment_illegality(state, attachment, host) -> Option<AttachIllegality>` returning `None` (legal) or a typed reason (`FilterOrZone`, `Protection`, `Prohibited`) \u2014 replacing the two divergent `bool` checks (`can_attach_to_object` and `is_valid_attachment_target`) so the cast/move-time gate and the SBA re-check can never drift again.\n- Fold into it: the Enchant-filter + zone check, `keywords::protection_prevents_from` (CR 702.16c/d), and the `CantBeAttached`/`CantBeEnchanted`/`CantBeEquipped` statics.\n- Keep the existing Aura-vs-Equipment SBA split: an illegal Aura is put into its owner's graveyard (CR 704.5m), an illegal Equipment/Fortification is unattached but stays on the battlefield (CR 704.5n).\n- Add fail-on-revert coverage: protection-from-color on an enchanted host detaches the Aura to the graveyard; protection-from-artifacts on an equipped host unattaches the artifact Equipment (stays on battlefield); `CantBeEnchanted` acquired post-attachment detaches; and legal attachments are unaffected.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-01T19:43:18.000Z",
